HEADWORD: Sircar
<hw>Sir*car"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind. & Per.
<ets>sark⟦amac⟧r</ets> a superintendant, overseer, chief; Per.
<ets>sar</ets> the head + <ets>k⟦amac⟧r</ets> action, work.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A Hindoo clerk or accountant.</def>
<mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A district or province; a circar.</def>
<mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The government; the supreme authority of the
state.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sirdar</ent>⟦br⟧
